This paper discusses the use of machine learning and social service interventions to reduce recidivism in the criminal justice system, which falls under the category of computational criminology (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the incorporation of predictive equity into machine learning decision making, which falls under the category of fairness in machine learning (cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning models in an operational public policy setting, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational social science (cs.CL).
